title: Why mega-cap tech stocks could rally another 15% by year-end under a Biden-helmed split government, according to Wedbush
text: A Joe Biden-led White House and Republican Senate is the "Goldilocks election outcome" that will send technology stocks higher into year-end 2020, according to Wedbush. In a Monday note, a team of analysts led by Dan Ives said that tech stocks could rally another 10%-15% by the year end, with FAANG stocks, cloud software stocks, and cyber security names leading the way.Â
